---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Affiliate Disclosure"
  description="New England Crust participates in affiliate marketing programs. Learn how we handle affiliate links and commissions."
>
  <section class="container-page py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="eyebrow">• Disclosure</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl text-balance md:text-5xl">Affiliate Disclosure</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-timber-200/70">Last updated: May 2026</p>

      <div class="prose prose-invert mt-8 max-w-none
                  prose-headings:font-display prose-headings:text-timber-50
                  prose-a:text-glow-200 hover:prose-a:text-glow-300">

        <p>
          New England Crust participates in affiliate marketing programs, which means we may earn
          a commission when you click a link on this site and make a purchase — at no additional
          cost to you.
        </p>

        <p>
          We are a participant in the Amazon Services LLC Associates Program, an affiliate
          advertising program designed to provide a means for sites to earn advertising fees by
          advertising and linking to Amazon.com. We may also earn commissions through programs run
          by Ooni, Solo Stove, SharkNinja, Williams Sonoma, Crate &amp; Barrel, Etsy (via Awin),
          Breville, ButcherBox, and other brands whose products we write about.
        </p>

        <h2>What this means in practice</h2>
        <p>
          Every product we recommend is something we have personally used, tested, or would
          genuinely buy ourselves. Affiliate relationships do not influence which products we
          recommend or what we write about them.
        </p>
        <p>
          When a link is an affiliate link, we do not label each one individually — but this
          disclosure page covers all such links site-wide, as required by the FTC.
        </p>

        <h2>How commissions work</h2>
        <p>
          If you click a link and buy something within the cookie window (typically 24 hours for
          Amazon, 30 days for most other programs), New England Crust receives a small percentage
          of the sale. The price you pay is identical whether you use our link or go directly to
          the retailer.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this disclosure or any recommendation on the site, reach us
          through the <a href="/about/">About page</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
